<h2>Study Note</h2>

<p>#1: <br>
Define a class Calc. This class has the following 18 methods.
- initialize
- to_s
- press_0, press_1, ..... , press_9
- press_clear
- press_add, press_sub, press_times, press_div
- press_equal</p>

<p>#2: <br>
Define a method initialize. This method is used once in the above code to create just one object at #9.</p>

<p>#3: <br>
Define a method to_s. In Shoes, para uses <code>to_s</code> implicitly at #10. If you comment out <code>to_s</code> definition lines, you will see the following output.</p>

<p><strong>simple-calc-1.png</strong></p>

<p><img src="http://github.com/ashbb/shoes_tutorial_html/raw/master/images/simple-calc-1.png" alt="simple-calc-1.png" /></p>

<p>#4: <br>
Define methods press_0, press_1, ..... , press_9 with the method <code>define_method</code>. See <code>ri Module#define_method</code>. They are the same as the following.</p>

